<h3>What is probability</h3>
In simplest terms it can be defined as, how likely something (an event) is expected to happen</p>
<!--b>&#x2119</b>P(An event) = ( number of favourable outcomes ) / ( total number of all possible outcome(s) )</p-->
<img src="/images/probabilityD.svg" width="440px" /></p>
<dl>
<dt>Ex.</dt>
<dd>Total number of all possible outcome(s) in a coin toss is 2 {Head,Tail} and for a dice roll it is 6 {1,2,3,4,5,6}</br>
Number of favourable outcome(s) for observing head in a coin toss, is 1={Head}.</br>
i.e., P(Head) = 1/2 {0.5 or 50%}</br>
<e>Thing to remember:</e> Total sum of the probabilities of all possible events in a given experiment is always 1.</br>
i.e., P(Head)+P(Tail) = 1</br>
Thus, P(Tail) = 1 - P(Head) = 0.5
</dd>
</dl>
<h3>Notations</h3>
